    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pak choi wedges</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 3-4 min or until the pak choi is fork tender</p><p>Once cooked, add your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>to the bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
